column2: How many months of your life would you sacrifice for a year without covid restrictions?
None.  Fuck you for not having that option.
1 month less (my QoL slightly improved due to COVID restrictions)
0 - there is nothing stopping me from living the way I want right now
More than year.  Fuck.  This.  Shit.  Democracy anyone?
O:  Not sure what restrictions you mean.  Also, many restrictions were largely optional.

the notion that suddenly everything would be back to normal absent public health restrictions is retarded and you should stop posting, you're literally an animal and you belong in a zoo. i dont give a shit what the official rules are, im not going to a crowded bar until im vaccinated because i'm not a fucking idiot, many others are like me in that they don't take pleasure in spreading covid and recognize that while this whole situation really sucks, it wasn't created in a lab to arbitrarily punish you. life isn't fair and then you die, snowflake.
I'm from burgerstan, but living in China for about 3 years. 3 months of restrictions was all that was necessary, and I am glad to have made that trade. Having my normal life back is really nice.
